				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The other night I turned myself into a Tree Stump in the middle of the misty thicket. I saw a bat walk by and while still being the tree stump I hit it with tashan and then proceeded to use the Melee attack (it was low blue, why waste mana?) and killed it rather easily.<BR>
<BR>
Quite common right? Well, after killing the bat, I discovered I could MOVE around! There I was, a tree stump, and I could move around as the tree stump. I went to the gate there and a high level druid thought it was hilarious a tree stump moving around and proceeded to SoW and Levitate me, so then I was a fast flying tree stump! As a Fast Flying Tree Stump I went around casting Strength on all the Newbies in the zone, I was having a blast and it lasted a pretty long time.<BR>
<BR>
I have not been able to duplicate this. But it was fun while it lasted.
